<div style=3D"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; =
margin-left: 0cm; "><b>P. Maret (LHC, Saint-Etienne) "Cultural reasoning"</=
b></div><div style=3D"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.=
0001pt; margin-left: 0cm; ">The globalized knowledge society generates virt=
ual enterprises that are usually set up and managed on the web, and the new=
 trend is to make the relevant technologies available on intelligent portab=
le devices. The existence of trust is a &nbsp;mandatory condition to make s=
uch enterprises successful. Trust has many facets ranging from very theoret=
ical ones to fully heuristic features. One point is that trust can arise wh=
en one understands the behavior of the other.<br></div><div style=3D"margin=
-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; ">=
<font class=3D"Apple-style-span" size=3D"3"><span class=3D"Apple-style-span=
" style=3D"font-size: 12px; "><b><span class=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"=
font-size: medium; font-weight: normal; ">In this work we outline a new tec=
hnology leading to the possibility to include &nbsp;inter-cultural issues a=
mong the factors having a strong impact on trust. &nbsp;This technology is =
called Abstraction-Based Information Technology. Its goal is to enable to d=
esign tools in artificial intelligence to perform so-called cultural reason=
ing that ensures better trust among inter-cultural communities. An argument=
 in favor of our approach is that it relies on a bottom-up approach, partic=
ularly suitable for the web technology and for intelligent wearable devices=
.</span></b></span></font></div><div style=3D"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right=
: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><br></b></div><div><=
b><span class=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"font-weight: normal; "><span cl=
ass=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"font-size: 12px; "><b>P.E. Portier &amp; =
S. Calabretto (LIRIS Lyon)&nbsp;</b></span><b>"DINAH, une plateforme philol=
ogique pour la construction de documents&nbsp;multistructur=E9s"</b><div st=
yle=3D"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm; margin-bottom:=
 0.0001pt; "><span class=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"line-height: 22px; "=
><span title=3D"reality (although an immersive environment could also be a =
complete fantasy or abstraction)." style=3D"background-color: rgb(255, 255,=
 255); "><span title=3D"specifically, on users' interactions with realistic=
 and engaging characters." style=3D"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); "=
><span title=3D"=95	Find a compromise between the requirement of the real l=
ife reference and the learning context." style=3D"background-color: rgb(255=
, 255, 255); "><span title=3D"=95	Create engaging interactions for players =
with realistic characters." style=3D"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); =
"><span title=3D"=95	Blur the line between the virtual and the real experie=
nces." style=3D"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); "><span title=3D"=95	=
Create engaging interactions for players with realistic characters." style=
=3D"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); "><font class=3D"Apple-style-span=
" size=3D"3"><span class=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"font-size: 12px; "><=
span class=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"font-size: medium; line-height: no=
rmal; ">Des usages diff=E9rents d'un m=EAme document peuvent introduire&nbs=
p;simultan=E9ment des structures concurrentes.&nbsp;Les travaux qui s'int=
=E9ressent =E0 la repr=E9sentation des documents&nbsp;multi-structur=E9s se=
 focalisent sur le probl=E8me de la repr=E9sentation des&nbsp;quasi-hi=E9ra=
rchies, mais ne s'occupent pas de la construction du document&nbsp;c'est-=
=E0-dire du processus qui fait apparaitre la multistructuralit=E9.&nbsp;Nou=
s d=E9fendons l'hypoth=E8se selon laquelle l'apparition d'une structure&nbs=
p;locale de graphe au sein de ce qui =E9tait un arbre fait signe de la&nbsp=
;n=E9cessit=E9 de distinguer deux structures au lieu d'une. C'est ce que&nb=
sp;permet notre interface de transcription.&nbsp;Par ailleurs, pour contr=
=F4ler, documenter et justifier l'apparition des&nbsp;vocabulaires structur=
ant, nous proposons une repr=E9sentation&nbsp;chronologique de la trace des=
 activit=E9s d'annotation. Cette trace est&nbsp;annotable. Des d=E9bats arg=
ument=E9s peuvent ainsi na=EEtre au sujet d'usages&nbsp;concurrents.</span>=
